One of them, the first prayer is how we ask Jesus to have mercy on us and close any doors we've opened.

36:48.007 --> 36:49.529
And the second one is about forgiveness.

36:50.370 --> 36:52.594
So I'm just gonna read the first one and it will be coming up now.

36:52.634 --> 36:54.677
You can take a photo and pray it later.

36:55.037 --> 37:01.266
Reads like this, Lord Jesus Christ of Nazareth, I, you say your name, confess, renounce and reject my involvement in

37:01.602 --> 37:06.248
and list whatever it is, lying, stealing, porn, slander, gossip, gluttony.

37:07.089 --> 37:16.301
I asked the Holy Spirit to close and seal all doors that may have been open to me or my family, seal them with the blood of Jesus, of the true Lord Jesus Christ, amen.

37:16.381 --> 37:17.702
In other words, shut that down.

37:19.384 --> 37:22.108
We need to take a stand against that.

37:23.209 --> 37:26.994
Now, I want to end with this verse, Ephesians 4, 31.

37:27.074 --> 37:36.584
Get rid of all bitterness and rage and anger and brawling and slander and malice and be kind and compassionate to one another, forgiving each other just as in Christ God forgave.

37:37.104 --> 37:37.325
You.

37:37.365 --> 37:45.613
Forgiveness is costly, it's hard, it's difficult, it takes time, it's not easy and it's critical.

37:46.834 --> 37:50.558
So here's a prayer I'd love lots of you to pray this week about forgiveness.

37:51.239 --> 37:54.162
So Satan doesn't get ground in our church.

37:54.722 --> 37:56.304
because of brokenness or relationships.

37:56.644 --> 37:57.265
This reads like this.

37:57.305 --> 37:58.907
Dear Heavenly Father, you can take the photo.

37:59.708 --> 38:03.192
I thank you that your kindness has led me to repentance.

38:03.873 --> 38:12.823
I have struggled to the extent that the same patience and kindness towards others who have offered me, sorry, let me read this again.

38:13.183 --> 38:22.514
Dear Heavenly Father, I thank you that your kindness has led me to repentance and I confess that I have struggled to extend that same patience and kindness towards others who have offended me

38:22.594 --> 38:34.867
But instead I have Harvard bitterness and resentment, I pray that during this time of self-examination, you'd bring to my mind those people that I have not forgiven in order that I may begin the process of forgiveness.

38:35.948 --> 38:38.731
And those I have heard are offended and I need to ask forgiveness of.

38:38.832 --> 38:42.235
Lord, I choose to begin the forgiveness process.

38:42.616 --> 38:47.000
And then it says, literally identify the offense because it made me feel.

38:47.281 --> 38:48.562
Say the word, what it made you feel.

38:48.930 --> 38:52.675
Lord, I release all these people to you and I release my right to seek revenge.

38:53.476 --> 38:56.020
I choose not to hold on to bitterness or anger.

38:56.460 --> 38:59.444
I ask you to heal my damaged emotions in Jesus name.

39:00.025 --> 39:00.265
Amen.

39:02.288 --> 39:09.538
You know, there's great hope for every church and there's great joy and peace offered.

39:10.519 --> 39:13.163
And there is great future for this local church.

39:13.844 --> 39:15.666
There is great future

39:15.970 --> 39:22.319
for our personal lives, our relational lives, our families, our friends, like nothing's beyond the love and beauty of God.

39:22.980 --> 39:24.622
But my encouragement this week is this.

39:25.743 --> 39:29.869
Would you be willing to pray a prayer where you say, God, get us in more trouble, not less?

39:30.871 --> 39:38.020
Would you be willing to say, Lord, am I actually even generous and actually change it so we can break the ceiling to move forward?

39:38.661 --> 39:45.010
And would you be willing to actually pray one of these two prayers or both of them, asking God to close doors that might have been open?

39:45.378 --> 39:49.383
and also teaching or learning to forgive and pray for others.

39:50.124 --> 39:52.888
So I'm just gonna pray the Holy Spirit works in these three avenues.

39:53.589 --> 39:56.313
So Father and Son send the Holy Spirit like you did in Acts 4.

39:57.114 --> 39:58.215
Move in great power.

39:59.237 --> 40:00.739
Help us to pray prayers we don't wanna pray.

40:00.759 --> 40:03.062
I help us to trust you.

40:03.963 --> 40:12.114
Lord, help generosity to now take place, because it's so many are generous in our church, but now may it become church wide.

40:13.250 --> 40:16.859
May there just be a real, unbelievable moment of generosity.

40:17.741 --> 40:22.373
And lastly, Lord, would you begin to close doors among us and teach us forgiveness?

40:23.275 --> 40:26.985
I'm asking you, Lord, in the next week to do unbelievable miracles among us.

40:27.125 --> 40:30.674
I ask this in Jesus' name and we all said, amen.

